    {
      "id": "line-000",
      "start": 0.0,
      "end": 5.68,
      "text": "This is a LibraVox recording, and all LibraVox recordings are in the public domain.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-001",
      "start": 6.66,
      "end": 11.22,
      "text": "For more information or to volunteer visit LibraVox.org.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-002",
      "start": 13.14,
      "end": 23.56,
      "text": "This is a recording by Kristen Luoma, green kri.com, ASOP's fables, the Fox and the Stork.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 25.94,
      "end": 32.98,
      "text": "A fox invited a stork to dinner at which the only fare provided was a large, flat dish of soup.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 34.08,
      "end": 41.0,
      "text": "The fox lapped it up with great relish, but the stork, with her long bill, tried in vain to partake of the savory broth.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 42.64,
      "end": 53.1,
      "text": "Her evident distress caused the sly fox much amusement, but not long after the stork invited him in turn and set before him a pitcher with a long and narrow neck",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 53.1,
      "end": 55.2,
      "text": "into which she could get her bill with ease.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 56.2,
      "end": 64.22,
      "text": "Thus, while she enjoyed her dinner, the fox sat by hungry and helpless, for it was impossible for him to reach the tempting contents of the vessel.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 66.62,
      "end": 68.72,
      "text": "End of the Fox and the Stork.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
